Israeli soldier killed in south Lebanon blast . One Israeli soldier was killed and three were wounded on Tuesday when guerrillas set off a roadside bomb near their patrol in south Lebanon , pro - Israeli militia sources said . The pro - Iranian Hizbollah guerrilla movement claimed responsibility for the attack . The sources said the blast occurred as Israeli soldiers were travelling on foot on the road between Marqaba and Odeissi deep in the central sector of the zone . Tuesday ' s casualties brought to 26 the number of Israeli soldiers killed in south Lebanon so far this year , three more than last year ' s total . On December 7 , Hizbollah guerrillas killed one Israeli soldier and wounded two in a similar attack . Hizbollah ( Party of God ) leads an Islamic Resistance committed to ousting Israeli troops from the 15 - km ( nine - mile ) south Lebanon border area . 
